///

/// Introduction

@node Introduction
@title "Introduction"


LogicSim is a program to simulate digital logic circuits.
It has a full graphic user interface to design and edit
the circuits.



Features:

    * @{"Scope" link SCOPE} with unlimited number of channels
    * grid
    - unlimited number of gates
    - user definable @{"work space" link WORKAREA}
    - @{"AND" link GATE_AND}, @{"OR" link GATE_OR}, @{"NAND" link GATE_NAND}, @{"NOR" link GATE_NOR} and @{"XOR" link GATE_XOR} gates with 2, 3 or 5 inputs
    - @{"RS" link GATE_RSFF}, @{"JK" link GATE_JKFF}, @{"JKMS" link GATE_JKMSFF}, @{"T" link GATE_TFF} and @{"D" link GATE_DFF} flip flops
    - @{"JKMS" link GATE_JKMSRSFF} and @{"T" link GATE_TRSFF} FlipFlops with independent Set and Reset inputs
    - user definable Timer: @{"Clock" link GATE_CLOCK}, @{"Monoflop" link GATE_MONO}, @{"turn on delay" link GATE_TOND} and
                            @{"turn off delay" link GATE_TOFFD}
    - saving the circuit as @{"iff" link SAVEIFF} or @{"print" link PRINT} it
    - @{"input inverter" link GATE_INPUTINV}
    - @{"traffic light model" link GATE_TRAFFICLIGHT}
    - @{"7 segment display" link GATE_NUMDISPLAY} in HEX or decimal
    - @{"highlighting" link HIGHLIGHT} of wires with HIGH while simulating
    - replacing "compatible" gates without removing them first
    - you can @{"label" link LABEL} your gates with selectable position and font
    - all windows are font sensitive and resizable
    - @{"UNDO" link UNDO} function
    - AmigaGuide online help with diagrams
    - it's localized (currently English, German, Swedish and Spanish)
    - @{"copy" link COPY}/@{"cut" link CUT}/@{"insert" link INSERT} function


    * New for version 1.1

@endnode

