///

/// Keyboard

@node KEYBOARD
@title "Keyboard equivalents"


These are only the shortcuts reachable without pressing the amiga
key. You can find the shortcuts for menu items in the menus themselves.


    gates
    -----

    a - @{"AND" link GATE_AND}                   A - @{"NAND" link GATE_NAND}
    o - @{"OR" link GATE_OR}                    O - @{"NOR" link GATE_NOR}
    x - @{"XOR" link GATE_XOR}                   n - @{"NOT" link GATE_NOT}
    s - @{"switch" link GATE_SWITCH}                l - @{"LED" link GATE_LED}
    1 - @{"HIGH" link GATE_HIGH}                  0 - @{"LOW" link GATE_LOW}


    editing
    -------

    c - @{"connect" link CONNECT}               d - @{"remove gate" link REMOVEGATE}
    r - @{"Start (run)" link START}           w - @{"remove wire" link REMOVEWIRE}
    u - @{"undo" link UNDO}                  2 - @{"2 inputs" link GATE_xInputs}
    3 - @{"3 inputs" link GATE_xInput}              5 - @{"5 inputs" link GATE_xInputs}

    SPACE - repeat last action



    drawing wires  (@{"connect" link CONNECT})
    -------------

    SPACE - set node to last point
    u - remove last part of wire (undo last click)
    ESC - abort drawing


    simulation
    ----------

    SPACE or p - @{"pause" link PAUSE} simulation
    ESC - abort simulation


@endnode

///

/// Hints

@node HINTS
@title "Hints"

  - Press space to repeat the last action. 

  - To follow long wires, you can click on the wire to
    highlight it.

  - To 'debug' circuits, turn the @{"'highlight HIGH wire'" link HIGHTLIGHT}
    item on. All wires with HIGH will be drawn white in
    simulation mode, so you can easily check if your
    circuit works as you want.

  - If you want to print your circuit, I recommend that you
    save it as iff and import it in your word processor.
    You will probably get a much better printing and you are
    able to include some text.

  - Click on a "basic gate" like @{"AND" link GATE_AND}, @{"NAND" link GATE_NAND}, @{"OR" link GATE_OR}, @{"NOR" link GATE_NOR}, @{"XOR" link GATE_XOR}
    to replace it with another one.


@endnode

